SIMPLE: redundancy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Redundancy
<hw>Re*dun"dan*cy</hw> <pr>(-d<it>a</it>n*s?)</pr>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>redundantia</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>redondance</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state of being redundant;
superfluity; superabundance; excess.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is redundant or in excess; anything
superfluous or superabundant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Labor . . . throws off <qex>redundacies</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>Surplusage inserted in a pleading
which may be rejected by the court without impairing the validity of
what remains.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Redundant</ent>⟦br⟧
